{
  "texts": [
    "Probabilistic Inference in AI SystemsProbabilistic inference has been increasingly recognized as a vital component in AI systems.",
    "Early applications focused on simple probabilistic models to enhance decisionmaking processes in AI [35].",
    "Such models later evolved to incorporate Bayesian networks, offering a more sophisticated approach to handle uncertainty in AI predictions [36,37].",
    "The integration of probabilistic inference in machine learning algorithms led to significant improvements in their predictive accuracy, especially in scenarios with incomplete or ambiguous data [38,39].",
    "In natural language processing, probabilistic models played a crucial role in disambiguating language and enhancing the semantic understanding of AI systems [35,40]."
  ]
}